<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-06-25T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-06-25T11:00:00-05:00" n="196" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d196">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">501.<gloss target="#t_BC1">BC</gloss>
                                Indonesia/6–2548: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Consulate General</gloss> at
                                    Batavia</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-06-25T12:00:00-04:00">June
                                        25, 1948—noon.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>291. <gloss target="#t_Usgoc1">Usgoc</gloss> 117. Dept disturbed
                                possibility precedent might be established by action <gloss target="#t_GOC1">GOC</gloss> in telegraphing <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> that Steering Committee meeting
                                stalemated over procedural issue (addendum to <gloss target="#t_GOC1">GOC</gloss> Report cabled June 22<note n="1" xml:id="d196fn1">Document S/850/Add.1, <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>, <hi rend="italic">3rd yr., Suppl.</hi> (June),
                                    p. 150.</note>). While this action fortunately did not prolong
                                discussion Lake Success, Dept believes desirable keep to the extent
                                    <pb facs="0284" n="270" xml:id="pg_270"/> possible this and
                                other contentious matters out of <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>
                                and hopes you can assist to this end.</p>
                            <p>Sent Batavia as 117, rptd The Hague as 275.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>